definition.value: A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of hyocholic acid 6-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-(S-[long-chain acyl]pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is an (7S)-7-hydroxy-C2-C8-saturated long-chain fatty acyl; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-(S-[long-chain acyl]pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is an (7R,8R)-7,8-dihydroxy-C2-C8-saturated long-chain fatty acyl; major species at pH 7.3.

Organic heterohexacyclic compounds that are diterpenoid trilactones found in the ginkgo tree (also known as the maidenhair tree, Ginkgo biloba). They have a cage skeleton consisting of six 5-membered rings (a spiro[4.4]nonane carbobicyclic ring, three lactones and a tetrahydrofuran ring) which includes a tert-butyl substituent. The ginkolides vary only in the number and positions of their hydroxy substituents.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 7-oxoheptanoyl. Major species at pH 7.3
An alpha-amino-acid residue cation obtained by protonation of the amino and imino nitrogens of N-(4-aminobutylidene)-L-lysine residue; major species at pH 7.3
A glycerophospholipid, where R1 and R2 are acyl chains and R3 any of the groups that represent the different phospholipid classes (choline, ethanolamine, glycerol, etc).

A glycerophospholipid that is a lysophospholipid where only R1 or R2 is an acyl chain, the other is a hydrogen, and R3 is any group that represents the different classes of glycerophospholipids (choline, ethanolamine, inositol, etc).
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 5alpha-dihydrotestosterone 17-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.
A fatty alcohol containing 12 carbons and 1 double bond.

A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 5alpha-dihydrotestosterone 17-O-[beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1->2)-glucuronide] arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-amino acid resulting from the formal condensation of carboxy group of isovaleric acid with the amino group of sarcosine.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid that is octadecapentaenoic acid in which the five double bonds are located at positions 2, 4, 6, 8 and 10 (the all-trans-geoisomer).
A isothiocyanate that is hexane in which two of the terminal methyl hydrogens at positions 1 and 6 have been replaced by isothiocyanato and methylsulfanyl groups.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 2,5-dihydroxybenzoic acid in which the phenolic hydrogen at position 2 has been replaced by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.
A desulfoglucosinolic acid resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of (3S)-N,3-dihydroxypent-4-enethioamide with beta-D-glucopyranose.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid derived from linoleic acid.
An O-acyl carbohydrate obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2-oxindole-3-acetic acid with the anomeric hydroxy group of beta-D-glucose.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxy-17beta-estradiol 3-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of indoles that is 1H-indole carrying methoxy and isothiocyanatomethyl substituents at positions 1 and 3 respectively.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxy-17beta-estradiol 2-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.
An apo carotenoid sesquiterpenoid that is 2-trans-abscisic acid in which the keto group at position 4' has been reduced to the corresponding alcohol.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the amino group of 4-methoxy-3-indolylmethylamine.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 4-hydroxy-17beta-estradiol 3-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 4-hydroxy-17beta-estradiol 4-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of indoles that is 1H-indole carrying isothiocyanatomethyl and methoxy substituents at positions 3 and 4 respectively.
An N-acyl-amino acid obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 6-hydroxyindole-3-acetic acid with the amino group of phenylalanine.
An indole phytoalexin that is camalexin in which the hydrogen at position 6 on the indole fragment has been replaced by a methoxy group.
A nitrile oxide that is pentane in which two of the terminal methyl hydrogens at positions 1 and 5 have been replaced by oxidonitrile and methylsulfanyl groups.
A glucosinolic acid that is glucoraphenin in which the hydroxy hydrogen at position 6 on the glucose fragment has been replaced by a sinapoyl group.
A member of the class of oxindoles that is 7-hydroxy-2-oxindole-3-acetic acid in which the phenolic hydrogen has been replaced by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.
A nitrile oxide that is hexane in which two of the terminal methyl hydrogens at positions 1 and 6 have been replaced by oxidonitrile and methylsulfanyl groups.
An omega-(methylsulfany)alkyl desulfoglucosinolate in which the omega-(methylsulfany)alkyl group is specified as 7-(methylsulfanyl)heptyl.
An isothiocyanate that is octane in which two of the terminal methyl hydrogens at positions 1 and 8 have been replaced by isothiocyanato and methylsulfanyl groups.
An S-substituted L-cysteine in which the thiol hydrogen of L-cysteine has been replaced by a 9-(methylthio)nonylhydroximoyl group.
A beta-D-glucoside that is coniferaldehyde in which the phenolic hydrogen has been replaced by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.
An omega-(methylsulfany)alkyl desulfoglucosinolate in which the omega-(methylsulfany)alkyl group is specified as 5-(methylsulfanyl)pentyl.
A desulfoglucosinolic acid resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of N-hydroxy-3-(methylsulfinyl)butanethioamide with beta-D-glucopyranose.
An omega-(methylsulfany)alkyl desulfoglucosinolate in which the omega-(methylsulfanyl)alkyl group is specified as 6-(methylsulfanyl)hexyl.
A desulfoglucosinolic acid resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of N-hydroxypent-4-enethioamide with beta-D-glucopyranose.
A desulfoglucosinolic acid resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of N-hydroxy-3-phenylpropanethioamide with beta-D-glucopyranose.
A desulfoglucosinolic acid resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of N-hydroxybut-3-enethioamide with beta-D-glucopyranose.
An omega-[(methylsulfiny)alkyl]glucosinolic acid in which the omega-(methylsulfinyl)alkyl group is specified as 6-(methylsulfinyl)hexyl.
